    "notes": "Detection should key on the parent process being an anomalous non-system executable (sync_agent.exe from ProgramData) spawning recovery-inhibiting binaries (vssadmin, bcdedit, wbadmin) with destructive argument patterns (/all /quiet, recoveryenabled No, delete catalog). Benign variants are distinguished by: (1) legitimate parent images from known software paths, (2) SYSTEM account vs. interactive user, (3) non-destructive sub-commands (list vs. delete). Consider chaining all three child-process spawns as a sequence correlation rule for higher-confidence alerting — any single event may FP, but all three from one parent within 60 seconds is high-confidence ransomware pre-staging behavior consistent with Fawkes run command chaining."
